9/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20319/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20319/canvas/1/14fcecf3-85a2-4c10-972d-46725bfa6e48","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:11:54.737Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The film similarly begins with Alma speaking to an unseen Dr. Hardy in this same firelit room. The “threat” of the doctor in their relationship has now also been quashed with Alma taking charge, and here Reynolds and Alma are seen alone together.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20319/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:445.6287380382773,41.622308612440236,929.8340311004787,794.7263755980861"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20319/canvas/1/98ef844b-0e9f-4cb3-ad62-91dacf7a5370","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:12:22.537Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Alma “replaces” Reynolds in her vision of their future together, he here wears an auburn sweater, creating a link to her dark red dresses. They have come together in a way previously impossible in their relationship.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20319/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:268.1788277511962,654.8213217703349,1106.1131877990429,403.8292464114834"}}}]}]}]}